Nine activists who were leaving a Decolonize This Place event at New York’s Artists Space on Saturday were attacked by a group of people of various ethnic backgrounds who claimed to be Donald Trump supporters.

Four or five men approached the activists as they were shouting slogans for various issues supported by Decolonize This Place—an action-oriented movement that advocates for indigenous peoples, black liberation, the human rights of Palestinians, global wage workers, and de-gentrification—including “Free Palestine” and“ Black Lives Matters.”
